What you need to know:

According to the latest Food and Agriculture Organisation (FAO) report on The State of Food Security and Nutrition in the World, in 2019, close to 690 million – or nearly one in 10 people in the world – were hungry.The Covid-19 pandemic could push an additional 130 million people worldwide into chronic hunger by the end of 2020.Timely and effective responses to the impact of Covid-19 depend upon knowing exactly where and when support is needed, as well as how that support can be implemented best.The pandemic is already generating an unprecedented impact on global and regional trade, with world merchandise trade in 2020 expected to fall by as much as 32 per cent.